The paper deals with real-time machine learning on data streams, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of several CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new learning algorithm and evaluates its performance on synthetic and real data. The second likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with adaptive learning and concept drift, which are important topics in AI. The third likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes a new algorithm for processing data streams efficiently. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with learning and adaptation, which are key topics in neural networks and evolutionary algorithms. The fifth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with real-time systems and control in the context of data streams.
